        "sender_full_name": "Jacob Lifshay",
        "timestamp": 1764140258
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>e.g.: <a href=\"https://github.com/WebAssembly/WASI/issues/25#event-21166962479\">https://github.com/WebAssembly/WASI/issues/25#event-21166962479</a></p>\n<div class=\"message_embed\"><a class=\"message_embed_image\" href=\"https://github.com/WebAssembly/WASI/issues/25#event-21166962479\" style=\"background-image: url(&quot;https://uploads.zulipusercontent.net/6b48751490c61d092cf40d9502668dae573f2e78/68747470733a2f2f6f70656e67726170682e6769746875626173736574732e636f6d2f353365323764383034656333366365313161333536366364396361646237363032363763633330383762333838613238343134626137663731343461323132332f576562417373656d626c792f574153492f6973737565732f3235&quot;)\"></a><div class=\"data-container\"><div class=\"message_embed_title\"><a href=\"https://github.com/WebAssembly/WASI/issues/25#event-21166962479\" title=\"System collation and system timezone data · Issue #25 · WebAssembly/WASI\">System collation and system timezone data · Issue #25 · WebAssembly/WASI</a></div><div class=\"message_embed_description\">(Maybe this is two separate issues?) It's common for runtimes (or apps) to have to bundle entire copies of collation tables, timezone data, etc with every app distributed. It adds a considerable am...</div></div></div>",
