    {
        "content": "<p>here's a much better example: <a href=\"https://github.com/WebAssembly/WASI/issues/56#event-21166968177\">https://github.com/WebAssembly/WASI/issues/56#event-21166968177</a></p>\n<div class=\"message_embed\"><a class=\"message_embed_image\" href=\"https://github.com/WebAssembly/WASI/issues/56#event-21166968177\" style=\"background-image: url(&quot;https://uploads.zulipusercontent.net/d400b9f68f0f410c1d2405e13bd5567c3809b747/68747470733a2f2f6f70656e67726170682e6769746875626173736574732e636f6d2f653639316338666366663130663434306130373138356362346335613639656665383765666463313639666563653731643834646534633134613862643434352f576562417373656d626c792f574153492f6973737565732f3536&quot;)\"></a><div class=\"data-container\"><div class=\"message_embed_title\"><a href=\"https://github.com/WebAssembly/WASI/issues/56#event-21166968177\" title=\"Blockchain call extension · Issue #56 · WebAssembly/WASI\">Blockchain call extension · Issue #56 · WebAssembly/WASI</a></div><div class=\"message_embed_description\">Most blockchain functions map well to WASI except for call/transact, which is an RPC augmented with the ability to transfer the platform's native token (e.g., Eth) from the caller to the callee. It...</div></div></div>",
        "id": 560317113,
