    {
        "content": "<p>I found three more that had been inadvertently closed:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/WebAssembly/WASI/issues/49\">https://github.com/WebAssembly/WASI/issues/49</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/WebAssembly/WASI/issues/38\">https://github.com/WebAssembly/WASI/issues/38</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/WebAssembly/WASI/issues/16\">https://github.com/WebAssembly/WASI/issues/16</a></li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"message_embed\"><a class=\"message_embed_image\" href=\"https://github.com/WebAssembly/WASI/issues/49\" style=\"background-image: url(&quot;https://uploads.zulipusercontent.net/5638c7e7c55df6667418d21fc45e46c679bef80b/68747470733a2f2f6f70656e67726170682e6769746875626173736574732e636f6d2f626262373163316364383438393432313164636534656462653462636439333364333936373765313636633331336161666365333865343735656136643035622f576562417373656d626c792f574153492f6973737565732f3439&quot;)\"></a><div class=\"data-container\"><div class=\"message_embed_title\"><a href=\"https://github.com/WebAssembly/WASI/issues/49\" title=\"WASI IPC module · Issue #49 · WebAssembly/WASI\">WASI IPC module · Issue #49 · WebAssembly/WASI</a></div><div class=\"message_embed_description\">Hey there, everyone! As I very briefly described in WebAssembly/wasi-sdk#33, WASI at the moment seems to be lacking support for IPC communication. I think that this feature is essential for some ap...</div></div></div><div class=\"message_embed\"><a class=\"message_embed_image\" href=\"https://github.com/WebAssembly/WASI/issues/38\" style=\"background-image: url(&quot;https://uploads.zulipusercontent.net/200990f1cf342c88e346e19bdc517611e78a4c03/68747470733a2f2f6f70656e67726170682e6769746875626173736574732e636f6d2f316239633166636233616339643064363963306637373034613130383962386538323563643465313961633734336264356636623035316166383831656466662f576562417373656d626c792f574153492f6973737565732f3338&quot;)\"></a><div class=\"data-container\"><div class=\"message_embed_title\"><a href=\"https://github.com/WebAssembly/WASI/issues/38\" title=\"Considerations for WASI standardization phases · Issue #38 · WebAssembly/WASI\">Considerations for WASI standardization phases · Issue #38 · WebAssembly/WASI</a></div><div class=\"message_embed_description\">Wasm has a phase process that describes how proposed features progress toward standardization. The process is designed to make it clear how to add to the wasm standard, both in terms of who should ...</div></div></div><div class=\"message_embed\"><a class=\"message_embed_image\" href=\"https://github.com/WebAssembly/WASI/issues/16\" style=\"background-image: url(&quot;https://uploads.zulipusercontent.net/8cbab6015cfdf9fa0932f0fda5ef953a698b88d9/68747470733a2f2f6f70656e67726170682e6769746875626173736574732e636f6d2f383830643265663862346565313666613064313166313865653839626466343334656333393265663438323666376633343637613562313436313233633666372f576562417373656d626c792f574153492f6973737565732f3136&quot;)\"></a><div class=\"data-container\"><div class=\"message_embed_title\"><a href=\"https://github.com/WebAssembly/WASI/issues/16\" title=\"Sharp edges of the current capability system · Issue #16 · WebAssembly/WASI\">Sharp edges of the current capability system · Issue #16 · WebAssembly/WASI</a></div><div class=\"message_embed_description\">So far it seems the most advanced practical capability system is Capsicum. I think it would be nice to correlate their API with WASI API just to avoid some potential mistakes (see e.g. fine grained...</div></div></div>",
        "id": 560390328,
        "sender_full_name": "Yosh Wuyts",
        "timestamp": 1764163775
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I found these by <a href=\"https://github.com/WebAssembly/WASI/issues?q=is%3Aissue%20state%3Aclosed%20sort%3Aupdated-desc\">filtering the issue list</a> to just the closed issues and then ordering by \"recently updated\". I think that should be all of them!</p>\n<div class=\"message_embed\"><a class=\"message_embed_image\" href=\"https://github.com/WebAssembly/WASI/issues?q=is%3Aissue%20state%3Aclosed%20sort%3Aupdated-desc\" style=\"background-image: url(&quot;https://uploads.zulipusercontent.net/c6ea8026d31b3f35a9a7e59888ba5e07c51cbf5c/68747470733a2f2f6f70656e67726170682e6769746875626173736574732e636f6d2f376163326331356634316131346633353930326636353834633530333135346166303432393530653465633430643139333835396430313830303665626462642f576562417373656d626c792f57415349&quot;)\"></a><div class=\"data-container\"><div class=\"message_embed_title\"><a href=\"https://github.com/WebAssembly/WASI/issues?q=is%3Aissue%20state%3Aclosed%20sort%3Aupdated-desc\" title=\"WebAssembly/WASI\">WebAssembly/WASI</a></div><div class=\"message_embed_description\">WebAssembly System Interface. Contribute to WebAssembly/WASI development by creating an account on GitHub.</div></div></div>",
